Substack&#x27;s essay applies as much to this tool as it does to webpack:<p><a href="https://gist.github.com/substack/68f8d502be42d5cd4942" rel="nofollow">https://gist.github.com/substack/68f8d502be42d5cd4942</a><p>Importantly, overloading require like this:<p><pre><code>  var collections = require(&#x27;npm:lodash-node/modern/collections&#x27;);
  var $ = require(&#x27;github:components/jquery&#x27;);
</code></pre>
... means that you can&#x27;t publish this module to npm and have the require statements work as expected.
